The paper discusses the use of graph databases and query languages, which falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques for graph analysis (cs.AI), deep learning for knowledge graph embeddings (cs.DL), and information retrieval for querying graph databases (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper presents an empirical evaluation of the performance of different graph databases, which could fall under the category of machine learning or data mining (cs.LG).
